# Homelab access — via operator workstation (SSH, HTTP/API, `P:`)

1. **How traffic moves:** The assistant runs commands in the **Cursor integrated terminal** on the **operator’s dev PC**. That PC is on the **lab LAN** (per **`docs/private/homelab/AGENT_LAB_ACCESS.md`** when present). There is **no separate “AI server”** dialing the house — **same effective access** as the operator’s shell: **`ssh`**, **`scp`/`sftp`**, **`curl`** to **`http://<host>:8088/`** (Data Boar default web port when applicable), etc.

1. **`read_file`** these when homelab / operator context applies (**no `@` required**; **`docs/private/`** ≠ GitHub):

   **`docs/private/homelab/AGENT_LAB_ACCESS.md`**, then **`docs/private/homelab/OPERATOR_SYSTEM_MAP.md`** (hardware + access + software chart), then **`docs/private/homelab/OPERATOR_RETEACH.md`**, then **`docs/private/homelab/HARDWARE_CATALOG.md`** if needed. Prefer **`ssh <linux-user>@<hostname>`** or **`Host` aliases** from **`~/.ssh/config`** (see **`docs/private.example/homelab/README.md`**). **Never** paste **passwords** or **private keys** into chat or **tracked** files.

1. **If a command fails:** DNS from dev PC, **`ping`**, **`ssh -v`**, **`sshd`** on target, **WSL vs Windows** `~/.ssh`, whether the service is listening (e.g. **8088**).

1. **Windows `P:` (pCloud):** **`P:\...`** is in scope on the dev PC when mounted — see **`AGENTS.md`**.

1. **Prefer running repo scripts over pasting one-liners** when the operator has configured SSH and a manifest: **`scripts/lab-op-sync-and-collect.ps1`**, **`scripts/collect-homelab-report-remote.ps1`** — see **`agent-autonomous-merge-and-lab-ops.mdc`**.

See **`docs/PRIVATE_OPERATOR_NOTES.md`** §4–§5, **`AGENTS.md`** (homelab + `P:`).
